metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #166
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: La Pedrera Serie 1 #151
metadata.description:
This project is inspired from Gaudí's Casa Milà in Barcelona, also known as La Pedrera. 

This is the first part of a 2-part-serie based on La Pedrera.

In this project, which is intentionaly saturated in color, you will recognize an abstract reproduction of the curved floors and windows of La Casa Milà.

The colors are accentued by the flowers disseminated on each floor. 

Main features of this project include:
- Palette: 10 colors,
- Texture: Strong or Soft,
- Noise: True or False,
- Strong Lines: True or False,
- Flower Packing: Mini or Maxi.

In live mode, press [s] to save a 1200 x 1500 (4 DPI) version of the mint.

Thanks a lot to everyone who will mint a token! :)

metadata.name: 99 recorridos #63
Intrusive Thoughts (on a loop) #31
metadata.description:
The concept for Intrusive Thoughts was born in the second half of 2022 during a series of therapy sessions.  Genuary 2023 played an important role on getting rid of most of my annoying intrusive thoughts.  Intrusive Thoughts (on a loop) is the first of four releases on the same topic.

Some browsers will need to tap or click to activate sound.  Use arrow up and arrow down to zoom or click on top and bottom.

metadata.name: Zug #73
metadata.description:
Zug is the German word for train, but it also translates to 'a force that pulls in a specific direction' which feels very fitting, though it might remain unclear in which direction exactly.

The image is build layering around 9000 transparent strokes grouped so that the resemblance of a passing train is created. Most strokes are blurred, some are repeating.

All editions share the same base color palette. From it three different palettes are derived for the light, medium and dark colors. Press 'c' to get a better idea of how this works.

Initial sketch made for the Weekly Creative Coding Challenge hosted by Raphaël de Courville (@Sableraph).

Commands:
f = fullscreen toggle
b = change window background color
c = color palettes overlay toggle
s = save image at 1080 x 1920 pixels
p = save image at 3240 x 5760 pixels

metadata.name: Bound #8
metadata.description:
Knots bind and hold, mark time, and unite. But the power of a well-tied knot isn't only to fasten – it also symbolizes how tightly one holds their pledges. Whether a commitment to a partner, community, or oneself – the longevity of a deeply held bond is often marked with a symbol of passing time, like knots tied in a rope.

Let these ropes remind us of the binds we hold – new ones, lengthy ones, unbreakable ones, and even those we’ve had to untie. In plain view, these knots invite us to contemplate what our bonds mean to us, and to see them anew.

---

Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution
Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution

Created with p5.js
For third party license information, please see license.md

---

TENDER x David Brice Allen
July 2022

metadata.name: Infinite Scaling System #17

metadata.name: Parametric Decoy #45
metadata.description:
The project started with the discovery of an unusual shape. Draw two parallel sine arcs and connect their opposite points. That's how you get one slice of Parametric Decoy. The shape may appear in its different phases. Sometimes elegant, sometimes awkward. Sometimes broken, sometimes symmetrical. Only connectivity stays the same.

Features:
- size: small, medium, large
- color: *several options*
- background: transparent, halftone, cutout
- distorted: no, maybe*, twisted, displaced, yes**

* "maybe" means I'm not quite sure if distortion affects visible part of the shape
** "yes" means combination of "twisted" and "displaced"

Press S to save. To download in custom size (ex. 2000px width), add &size=2000 to url, reload and press S.

Made with p5js, inspired by pop-art collages and my own geometric sketches

metadata.name: Knowledge #92
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
March 2023

***
This token was created for THE PASSAGE: Pitch Drop experience, an interactive minting experience where your choices determine the design of your token.

To take part, please purchase an Edition 5 Coin on fx(hash) by HERE & NOW. The artwork and experience draw inspiration from the 'The Pitch Drop Experiment': the world's longest-running laboratory experiment. Since 1927, only nine drops of pitch have fallen, and it has never been witnessed live.
***

What does it mean to "know" something? Just because we do not see it does not mean it is not there. It does not mean it is not happening. Many things take time and energy to happen and to be understood. 

Look at how long it takes for rocks to become sand and how ephemeral we are in the passage of time like drops in a waterfall that evaporate within a few seconds.

But they blend, collide, and hit a rock or two before they disappear. These are the moments that I cherish, that I find meaning from, even if no one will remember them. After all, it is small drops that turn rock into sand. It is grains of sand that change the surface of the Earth. 

## Guide
- For reliable playback, keep the window active and use IPFS view.  
- Tested on MacOS 13.2.1 with Chromium 110.0

## Keyboard Interaction  
- [spacebar] to play/pause.  
- [s] to save PNG.  

## URL Parameters  
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&w=1200&h=600  
- [w] and [h]: set width and height in pixels. (ex. w=1200&h=600)  
- [loop]: play as a loop. you can add a number to randomize. (ex. loop=1234) 
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 for hi-DPI screens.

### License

Refer to the included LICENSE.md for third-party library license information.

metadata.name: Primordial #31
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Drei #37
metadata.description:
For Lia Drei (https://www.archivioguerrieridrei.com/biografia-1?lang=en)

This morning I thought about all the work I did with triangles... the idea came to me that the right triangle is the symbol of creation...(…)
The hypotenuse is the love that unites and gives life. The tip of the triangle is the uterus which makes the space grow.
-- LIA DREI (Diaries, 2004)

My paintings have no past, they are empty of meaning in the present, but await the discussions of the future, as remotely as possible.
And this is why they don't have their feet firmly planted in the ground, although there are invisible roots that take life from the earth, like so many blades of grass.
While I work I look for the truth in what I do. The time is not yesterday because it would be false, it is not today because the emotion takes my breath away and I die every moment and am reborn after every new brushstroke.
Soon after, time becomes old, useless, meaningless. I never know what will come out with the next brushstroke or spatula stroke.
My thoughts go at supersonic speed and only stop to choose another color. The one just painted is never the right one. So I live the life of the new painting with the sense of mystery that the moonless night has. (…)
-- LIA DREI (Notes, 1962)

----

I never talk about myself.

I'm not creative.
I blatantly steal other people's art.
I'm a bad coder, I copy, paste, mix ideas.
I often ruin it, degrade it.
But I always make it mine what I like.

I absorb.

-- ALESSANDRO FIORE (fxhash, 2024)


—————

The work is created responsive by default and it will adapt to the browser window. It will change (even consistently in some cases) based on the screen aspect ratio.

Key commands:

1 = Square 2000x2000
2 = Square 4000x4000
3 = Square 6000x6000 (Dependent on your browser limitations, tested on Safari (Mac))
p = Portrait 1500x2115
l = Landscape 2115x1500
e = Responsive/Default
f = Fullscreen
s = Save as image


See LICENSE.txt in live view for licensing details.
